        <h1>Ethical Dilemmas: Preferential Treatment</h1>

<table style="width:100%">

<h2>Giving In: </h2>

  <tr>
    <th>Pros:</th>
    <th>Cons:</th> 

  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>Keeps a great relationship with the friend. </td>
    <td>Not morally correct. </td>

  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>You feel closer with your friend.</td>
    <td>You stray away from the people you didn't choose, even if they were  just random people. </td>

  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>You feel better about yourself. </td>
    <td>You feel guilty for the people you didn't pick.</td>
  </tr>
</table>

<h2>Keeping your decision: </h2>
<table style="width:100%">

  <tr>
    <th>Pros:</th>
    <th>Cons:</th> 

  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>Morally correct. </td>
    <td>Friend could be unhappy or possibly mad with your decision. </td>

  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>You feel good for the people you did pick. </td>
    <td>You feel guilty that you didn't give in to your friend. </td>
</tr>

</table>
